Network Interface (ENI)

What is ENI?

ENI (Elastic Network Interface) is a virtual network card attached to an EC2 instance.

Simple Definition

ENI is the network adapter that allows an EC2 instance to communicate with the network.

Real-Life Example

Think of your laptop.

Your laptop has a Wi-Fi/Ethernet adapter to connect to the internet.

Similarly,

EC2 Instance → ENI → Network

ENI Contains
Private IP Address
Elastic IP (Optional)
MAC Address
Security Group
Why Do We Use ENI?
Connect EC2 to the VPC.
Assign multiple private IPs.
Attach or detach ENIs between EC2 instances (same Availability Zone).
Easy Way to Remember

ENI = Network Card of EC2

