Elastic IP Address (EIP)
What is Elastic IP?

An Elastic IP (EIP) is a static public IPv4 address provided by AWS.

Simple Definition

Elastic IP is a permanent public IP address that you can associate with an EC2 instance.

Why Do We Need Elastic IP?

Normally, when you stop and start an EC2 instance, its public IP changes.

If users or applications connect using the old IP, they will fail.

An Elastic IP solves this problem because it does not change.

Real-Life Example

Imagine your house address changes every week.

Nobody can find your house.

Instead, you keep one permanent address.

That permanent address is like an Elastic IP.

Features
Static Public IPv4 Address.
Can be associated with one EC2 instance at a time.
Can be moved from one EC2 instance to another.
Remains the same even after the instance is stopped and started.

